Call Center Call Volume Forecasting — Time Series Case Study
Overview
This case study is not just about forecasting numbers — it’s about capturing the story of technological disruption:
AI reduces repetitive human tasks.
Companies profit from efficiency gains.
Human roles evolve, requiring reskilling and adaptation.
By highlighting both the technical rigor and the social impact, this project resonates with recruiters, industry leaders, and professionals navigating the AI revolution.
This project focuses on forecasting daily call volumes for an Indian call center over the next 30 days using three advanced time series techniques:

LSTM (Long Short-Term Memory networks)
ARIMA (AutoRegressive Integrated Moving Average)
XGBoost (Extreme Gradient Boosting adapted for time series regression)

The dataset spans from 01 Jan 2020 to present, with clean, imputed values and engineered features (lag variables, rolling means). 
Forecasts are generated to support operational planning, workforce optimization, and technology adoption strategies.

